ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC S3 <CONFIG="file-path"> <KEYID="aws-key-id"> <SECRET="aws-secret"> <NOSSL> <REGION="aws-region"> ;
     COPY "source-s3-location" "destination-s3-location";
     CREATE "bucket-name";
     DELETE "s3-location";
     DESTROY "bucket-name";
     GET "s3-location" <"local-path">;
     GETDIR "s3-location" "local-path";
     INFO "s3-location";
     LIST <_SHORT_> "s3-location";
     MKDIR "s3-location";
     PUT "local-path" "s3-location";
     PUTDIR "local-path" "s3-location";
     RMDIR "s3-location";
  RUN;

The S3 procedure is used for managing objects in Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3). 

The S3 procedure can be used for object management functions. For example, you can create buckets 
and add files to S3 with the procedure. If you want to analyze data that is in S3, then this is not 
the correct procedure to use. (Hint: You need to use CAS with a caslib that uses S3 as its data source.) 

Very important: Before you can use the S3 procedure, you need an AWS key ID and secret.

For more information about S3, see Amazon's S3 documentation:
http://aws.amazon.com/documentation/s3/
